Wash and dry produce.

Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}. Halve, core, and thinly slice or dice @apple{1} (whichever your kid prefers!). Thinly slice @mini cucumber{1} into rounds. Cut @Belgian waffle{1} into 1-inch-thick strips.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Add @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon} and pineapple to bowl with chicken; toss to coat.

Arrange @flour tortillas{6} on a clean work surface. Add chicken mixture to bottom half of each tortilla. Top with @mozzarella cheese{1%cup}.

Fold tortillas in half to create pizza-dillas.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add pizza-dillas and cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}. (Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches, adding a drizzle of oil for each batch.)

To serve: Halve pizza-dillas. Divide between plates and serve with apple slices, cucumber slices, and waffle sticks.

To stash: Let pizza-dillas cool completely before halving. Refrigerate pizza-dillas, apple slices, cucumber slices, and waffle sticks in separate containers and pack as desired!

== Grilled Cheese Dippers ==

Fill @sourdough bread{4%slice} with @cheddar cheese{1%cup} to form sandwiches.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 6 servings) in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium heat. Once butter has melted, add sandwiches and cook until bread is golden and cheese melts slightly, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (Work in batches if necessary, adding more butter for each batch.)

Cut sandwiches crosswise into 1-inch-thick strips. Divide between plates and serve with @marinara cup{2.5%ounce}, @buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%ounce}, and @guacamole{4%tablespoon} on the side for dipping.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.